# Ground truth
x0 = np.arange(-2, 2, .1)
x1 = np.arange(-2, 2, .1)
x0, x1 = np.meshgrid(x0, x1)
y_truth = ((x0**2)/22) - ((x1**2)/13) + 2.234235

ax = plt.figure().add_subplot(projection='3d')
ax.set_xlim(-2, 2)
ax.set_ylim(-2, 2)
ax.set_xticks(np.arange(-2, 2.01, .5))
ax.set_yticks(np.arange(-2, 2.01, .5))
surf = ax.plot_surface(x0, x1, y_truth, rstride=1, cstride=1, color='green', alpha=0.5)
plt.show()
In [8]:
rng = check_random_state(0)

# Training samples
X_train = rng.uniform(-2, 2, 100).reshape(50, 2)
y_train = ((X_train[:, 0]**2)/22) - ((X_train[:, 1]**2)/13) + 2.234235

# Testing samples
X_test = rng.uniform(-2, 2, 100).reshape(50, 2)
y_test = ((X_train[:, 0]**2)/22) - ((X_train[:, 1]**2)/13) + 2.234235
In [9]:
est_gp = SymbolicRegressor(population_size=50000,
                           generations=100, stopping_criteria=0.01,
                           p_crossover=0.7, p_subtree_mutation=0.1,
                           p_hoist_mutation=0.05, p_point_mutation=0.1,
                           max_samples=0.9, verbose=1,
                           parsimony_coefficient=0.00005, random_state=0)
est_gp.fit(X_train, y_train)

In [12]:
y_gp = est_gp.predict(np.c_[x0.ravel(), x1.ravel()]).reshape(x0.shape)
score_gp = est_gp.score(X_test, y_test)
y_tree = est_tree.predict(np.c_[x0.ravel(), x1.ravel()]).reshape(x0.shape)
score_tree = est_tree.score(X_test, y_test)
y_rf = est_rf.predict(np.c_[x0.ravel(), x1.ravel()]).reshape(x0.shape)
score_rf = est_rf.score(X_test, y_test)

fig = plt.figure(figsize=(12, 10))

for i, (y, score, title) in enumerate([(y_truth, None, "Ground Truth"),
                                       (y_gp, score_gp, "SymbolicRegressor"),
                                       (y_tree, score_tree, "DecisionTreeRegressor"),
                                       (y_rf, score_rf, "RandomForestRegressor")]):

    ax = fig.add_subplot(2, 2, i+1, projection='3d')
    ax.set_xlim(-2, 2)
    ax.set_ylim(-2, 2)
    ax.set_xticks(np.arange(-2, 2.01, .5))
    ax.set_yticks(np.arange(-2, 2.01, .5))
    surf = ax.plot_surface(x0, x1, y, rstride=1, cstride=1, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    points = ax.scatter(X_train[:, 0], X_train[:, 1], y_train)
    if score is not None:
        score = ax.text(-.7, 1, .2, "$R^2 =\/ %.6f$" % score, 'x', fontsize=14)
    plt.title(title)

plt.show()
